Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
flattenPartition(25.10)                                flattenPartition(25.10)

Name
       flattenPartition  -  Uncommits  (flattens) the partition back to normal
       module status

Syntax
       flattenPartition

       [-help]

       [<partition_name>]

       [-bringBackRow]

       [-keepPinGeometry]

       [-noUninheritPhysical]

       Uncommits (flattens) the partition back to normal module  status.  This
       command  should also be used to unassign blackbox pins after the black-
       box is committed. To unassign blackbox pins before the blackbox is com-
       mitted, use the setPtnPinStatuscommand. This command  unassigns  parti-
       tion  pins  as well. To bring back row information for a partition, use
       the -bringBackRow parameter. If the partition rows are non-integer-mul-
       tiple-height rows or are not aligned with the top-level rows, the flat-
       tenPartition command will automatically create a power  domain  associ-
       ated with the partition. The power domain will have the following char-
       acteristics:

              * The timing library will the same as that for the top level.

              * If  a global net connection is defined in the partition block,
                the power domain will have the  same  global  net  connection.
                Otherwise  the global net connection for the power domain will
                be set to the top-level net connection.

              * The minimum gap values will be the same as the placement  halo
                values for the partition.

       The recommended use model for bringing back non-integer-multiple height
       rows or unaligned rows is as follows.

       Top-down flow:

              * Create a power domain at full chip-level design.

              * Specify the same hierarchical instance as the partition

       Bottom-up flow:

              * Create a power domain at top-level design.

              * Assign the instance block as a member of the power domain cre-
                ated in step 1.

       The  flattenPartition  command  supports partitions with FlexModels. It
       restores back FlexModel information if the committed  partition  has  a
       FlexModel netlist.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each flattenPartition parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man flattenPartition

       -bringBackRow
              Specifies that partition row information should be brought  back
              for cases where:

              * the  partition  is  not  a power domain and row information in
                partition is different from top-level design, and

              * after uncommiting the partition, the  rows  of  the  partition
                space are not aligned with the top-level rows

              When  you  use this parameter, a power domain is created for the
              partition.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, the row  informa-
              tion is not brought back in such cases.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -keepPinGeometry
              Specifies  that  for every partition pin, a DRCFILL metal of the
              type special route is placed on top of the partition pins.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -noUninheritPhysical
              Specifies that physical only cell instances are  removed  during
              flattenPartition.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <partitionName>
              Specifies  the  name(s) of the partition(s). You can specify any
              number of partitions.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command uncommits  the  partition  status  of  partitions
       sheet17 and sheet25:

       flattenPartition sheet17 sheet25

